# Lambda LAP — Cline Rules

## Project

Lambda LAP (SigmaLoop) — Full-stack educational platform for learning programming.

## Structure

- `Backend/` — Node.js + Express v5 + TypeScript + MongoDB/Mongoose. API at localhost:4000/api/v1.
- `Frontend/` — React 19 + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS. SPA at localhost:5173.
- `Graduation Project/` — Reference docs only (API contract, DB schema, UI mockups). Do NOT modify.

## Backend Rules

- Entry: `Backend/src/server.ts` → `src/app.ts`
- MVC: models/ → controllers/ → routes/ → routes/index.ts
- Always use JSend helpers: `success(data)`, `error(msg, code?, details?)`
- Auth: `authenticate` middleware for JWT, `authorize('ROLE')` for role checks
- 3 roles: STUDENT, INSTRUCTOR, ADMIN
- Models: User, Course, Lesson, Challenge, Enrollment, LessonProgress, Submission, ChatThread, ChatMessage
- Config from env: PORT, DATABASE_URL, JWT_SECRET, JWT_EXPIRES_IN, NODE_ENV
- Tests: Jest + Supertest in `src/__tests__/`
- Style: ESLint Standard + TS, single quotes, 100 char width

## Frontend Rules

- Entry: `Frontend/src/main.tsx` → `src/App.tsx`
- Auth: `useAuth()` from `contexts/AuthContext.tsx` (Context API + localStorage JWT)
- API calls: Always use Axios instance from `services/api.ts` (auto-attaches Bearer token)
- Types: Define in `types/api.ts`
- Pages: `pages/<Name>/<Name>.tsx`, sub-components alongside
- UI primitives: `components/ui/` — no business logic
- Layouts: `components/layouts/` — MainLayout, AuthLayout, LessonLayout, AdminLayout
- Styling: Tailwind utilities, custom: `.glass-panel`, `.glass-card`, `.text-gradient`
- Tests: Vitest + @testing-library/react
- Style: ESLint recommended + TS, double quotes, 80 char width

## Supported Languages (Challenge System)

Python, C++, Java, JavaScript, TypeScript, Go, Rust

## Important

- Code execution controller is a dummy — returns mock results
- Rate limiting exists but is disabled
- Frontend API URL hardcoded in services/api.ts
- Graduation Project/Backend/api.md has the full API contract (v3.0)
- Graduation Project/Database/DB.pdf has the database schema
